{
  "texts": [
    "Recent adaptations of LLMs in the clinical domain emphasize their potential in understanding medical language.",
    "Noteworthy recent works [7,9,[39][40][41][42] use open-source datasets and display the performance of LLMs in multiple summarization tasks in medicine: radiology reports, patient health questions, progress notes, doctor-patient conversations, and discharge summaries.Other works [8,43] further explore domain adaptation of LLMs in the clinical domain through fine-tuning for improved performance in medical tasks.",
    "Our benchmark shows that open-source LLMs can produce high-quality BHCs and that Llama2-12/1813 B comes out as a superior choice for further analysis of open-source LLMs based on its performance and an expanded context length window (Figure 3a).",
    "The subgroup analysis (Figure 3b) further emphasizes the importance of a multi-faceted analysis when evaluating models.",
    "Furthermore, our context-length analysis (Figure 4) showcases the benefit of fine-tuning LLMs on datasets with a wide range of context lengths."
  ]
}